Maintainer: Richard Layton <graphdoctor@gmail.com>
Description: Provides tools and demonstrates methods for working with 
    individual undergraduate student-level records (registrar's data) in 'R'. 
    Tools include filters for program codes, data sufficiency, and timely 
    completion. Methods include gathering blocs of records, computing 
    quantitative metrics such as graduation rate, and creating charts to 
    visualize comparisons. 'midfieldr' interacts with practice data provided in 
    the 'midfielddata' package or with any data structure modeled on the 
    MIDFIELD database. The development of 'midfieldr' and 'midfielddata' was 
    supported by the US National Science Foundation through grant numbers 
    1545667 and 2142087.
